Signature of constructor of ClientConfig class changed between 4.14.0 and 4.13.0 version. That class is from `selenium-http` dependency, which is transitive dependency from `selenium-remote-driver`, on which appium is dependent on.

In their  file, they set the dependency to the latest in given range -&gt; [*build.gradle*][1]

So, without any changes to your dependencies, transitive dependency changed and is crashing your run.

Based on: [*transitive-dependencies-management.md*][2]

you can hardcode version to 4.13 which should fix the problem.
Example, in your pom.xml:

    &lt;dependencies&gt;
		&lt;dependency&gt; &lt;!-- explicitly download correct dependency --&gt;
			&lt;groupId&gt;org.seleniumhq.selenium&lt;/groupId&gt;
			&lt;artifactId&gt;selenium-remote-driver&lt;/artifactId&gt;
			&lt;version&gt;4.13.0&lt;/version&gt;
		&lt;/dependency&gt;
		&lt;dependency&gt;
			&lt;groupId&gt;io.appium&lt;/groupId&gt;
			&lt;artifactId&gt;java-client&lt;/artifactId&gt;
			&lt;version&gt;8.5.1&lt;/version&gt;
			&lt;exclusions&gt;
				&lt;exclusion&gt;  &lt;!-- exclude what appium is downloading --&gt;
					&lt;groupId&gt;org.seleniumhq.selenium&lt;/groupId&gt;
					&lt;artifactId&gt;selenium-remote-driver&lt;/artifactId&gt;
				&lt;/exclusion&gt;
			&lt;/exclusions&gt;
		&lt;/dependency&gt;
	&lt;/dependencies&gt;


  [1]: https://github.com/appium/java-client/blob/9176e8ead6ae19116713d8eb4fd15958bca4f4ca/build.gradle#L43
  [2]: https://github.com/appium/java-client/blob/v8.5.1/docs/transitive-dependencies-management.md

