your config `broker.addConnector(&quot;tcp://localhost:61616?broker.persistent=false&quot;);` is wrong, this is can be done only if you create a broker using `ActiveMQConnectionFactory`. See details [here][1]:

&gt; Using ActiveMQConnectionFactory
&gt; An embedded broker can also be created using an ActiveMQConnectionFactory and using a vm connector as a uri. e.g.
&gt; ```
&gt; ActiveMQConnectionFactory cf = new ActiveMQConnectionFactory(&quot;vm://localhost?broker.persistent=false&quot;);
&gt; ```

try
```java
@Bean
public BrokerService broker() throws Exception {
   BrokerService broker = new BrokerService();
   broker.addConnector(&quot;tcp://localhost:61616&quot;);
   broker.setPersistent(false);
   return broker;
}
```

  [1]: https://activemq.apache.org/how-do-i-embed-a-broker-inside-a-connection.html#HowdoIembedaBrokerinsideaConnection-UsingActiveMQConnectionFactory

